Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Cut the @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%g} into thirds.

Zest and cut the @lime{1} into wedges.

== Noodles ==

Pour the boiled water (see pantry for amount) into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} and bring back to the boil on high heat.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @egg noodle nest{125%g} and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

== Stir-Fry ==

While the noodles cook, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%g}, @sliced mushrooms{120%g}, pepper and broccoli. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir-fry until the chicken is cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Stir in the @Thai style spice mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and @ginger, garlic & lemongrass puree{15%g}. Cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @soy sauce{25%ml}, @Ketjap manis{50%g}, @honey{15%g} and @water for the sauce{50%ml} to the pan.

> If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Stir to combine and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the cooked noodles and a good squeeze of lime juice from a lime wedge to the pan. Toss to coat in the sauce, ~{1%minute}.

When ready, share your chicken stir-fry between your #serving bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the lime zest and serve with any remaining lime wedges for squeezing over.

Enjoy!